quran[18]{c,v,t,f}:
  89,25,"So on that Day, none will punish [as severely] as His punishment,"
  89,26,"And none will bind [as severely] as His binding [of the evildoers]."
  89,27,"[To the righteous it will be said], "
  90,19,"But they who disbelieved in Our signs - those are the companions of the left.{1}",footnotes:1:Or "the companions of ill fortune," i.e., those who receive their records in their left hands and proceed to Hell.
  90,20,"Over them will be fire closed in.{1}",footnotes:1:The cover over Hell will be sealed and locked, containing its fire and its inhabitants.
  92,13,"And indeed, to us belongs the Hereafter and the first [life]."
  92,14,"So I have warned you of a Fire which is blazing."
  92,15,"None will [enter to] burn therein except the most wretched one"
  93,10,"And as for the petitioner,{1} do not repel [him].",footnotes:1:Anyone who seeks aid or knowledge.
  93,11,"But as for the favor of your Lord, report [it]."
  94,7,"So when you have finished [your duties], then stand up [for worship]."
  94,8,"And to your Lord direct [your] longing."
  95,4,"We have certainly created man in the best of stature;{1}",footnotes:1:i.e., upright, symmetrical, and balanced in form and nature.
  95,5,"Then We return him to the lowest of the low,{1}",footnotes:1:This can refer to the depths of Hell, to decrepit old age or to immorality.
  95,6,"Except for those who believe and do righteous deeds, for they will have a reward uninterrupted."
  96,1,"Recite in the name of your Lord who created"
  96,2,"Created man from a clinging substance."
  96,3,"Recite, and your Lord is the most Generous -"